tspan.tspan: See your user’s experience of their day through their eyes
with the User Clock Sketch. This is a human-centered
approach visualizing the ‘customer journey’ by mapping to
the user’s point-of-view. It maps the actions of a particular
user type from the point where they wake up in the
morning, to the point where they go to sleep.
Draw your user type in the centre of a big circle
Draw a vertical line from the user type up to where the
‘12’ would normally go on a clock. This is the point where
your user type wakes up.
Draw radiating lines around the face of your ‘clock’.
Each line will separate a particular ‘stage of the day’ that
matters to that user type and their role.
Overlay your product’s/service’s context. On post-its
list up product tasks that the user type needs to get done
using your product at that particular time of the day.
Either individually or as a group, you can explore the
‘clock’ you have drawn as a map of time, to provoke more
insightful questions and enrich your understanding of
your users.
